`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
- **WaterEntity minimal interface**: The `tickWaterParticles` function takes `World<WaterEntity>` rather than `World<Entity>` — this lets tests pass a `World<WaterEntity>` directly without any casting, while production code casts `world as unknown as World<WaterEntity>`. Structural subtype + single cast at callsite.
- **Splash as one-shot burst**: The splash emitter is created once on `above→submerged` transition and tracked in state but never explicitly removed — the particle renderer handles lifetime expiry. Bubbles emitter IS removed when player exits water since it's continuous.
- **Config-driven particle params**: Both `buildSplashEmitter` and `buildBubblesEmitter` read from `config/game/procedural.json`, keeping all tuning values out of source code (follows the no-magic-numbers rule).
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`
